        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Stop Taxing the Second Amendment Act of 2016</b></p> <p>This bill prohibits a state or local government from imposing a tax on a firearm or ammunition sale that affects interstate commerce.</p> <p>Additionally, it prohibits a state or local government from imposing a new tax or increasing an existing tax on a background check incident to a firearm or ammunition sale.<br /></p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Stop Taxing the Second Amendment Act of 2016</title>
    <titles>
      <item>
        <titleType>Display Title</titleType>
        <title>Stop Taxing the Second Amendment Act of 2016</title>
      </item>
      <item>
        <titleType>Official Title as Introduced</titleType>
        <title>To limit the authority of States and local governments to impose taxes payable with respect to the sale of certain firearms or ammunition, or to impose new or increased taxes payable for background checks incident to sales of firearms or ammunition.</title>
        <billTextVersionName>Introduced in House</billTextVersionName>
